00194 static void rna_Constraint_name_set(PointerRNA *ptr, const char *value)
00195 {
00196     bConstraint *con = ptr->data;
00197     char oldname[sizeof(con->name)];
00198     
00199     /* make a copy of the old name first */
00200     BLI_strncpy(oldname, con->name, sizeof(con->name));
00201     
00202     /* copy the new name into the name slot */
00203     BLI_strncpy_utf8(con->name, value, sizeof(con->name));
00204     
00205     /* make sure name is unique */
00206     if (ptr->id.data) {
00207         Object *ob = ptr->id.data;
00208         ListBase *list = get_constraint_lb(ob, con, NULL);
00209         
00210         /* if we have the list, check for unique name, otherwise give up */
00211         if (list)
00212             unique_constraint_name(con, list);
00213     }
00214     
00215     /* fix all the animation data which may link to this */
00216     BKE_all_animdata_fix_paths_rename(NULL, "constraints", oldname, con->name);
00217 }

00287 static EnumPropertyItem *rna_Constraint_target_space_itemf(bContext *UNUSED(C), PointerRNA *ptr,
00288                                                            PropertyRNA *UNUSED(prop), int *UNUSED(free))
00289 {
00290     bConstraint *con = (bConstraint*)ptr->data;
00291     bConstraintTypeInfo *cti = constraint_get_typeinfo(con);
00292     ListBase targets = {NULL, NULL};
00293     bConstraintTarget *ct;
00294     
00295     if (cti && cti->get_constraint_targets) {
00296         cti->get_constraint_targets(con, &targets);
00297         
00298         for (ct = targets.first; ct; ct = ct->next)
00299             if (ct->tar && ct->tar->type == OB_ARMATURE)
00300                 break;
00301         
00302         if (cti->flush_constraint_targets)
00303             cti->flush_constraint_targets(con, &targets, 1);
00304 
00305         if (ct)
00306             return target_space_pchan_items;
00307     }
00308 
00309     return space_object_items;
00310 }
